node_modules/mongodb/README.md:23:### Release Integrity
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:24:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:25:Releases are created automatically and signed using the [Node team's GPG key](https://pgp.mongodb.com/node-driver.asc). All release packages provided as part of a GitHub release are signed. To verify the provided packages, download the key and import it using gpg:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:26:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:27:```shell
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:28:gpg --import node-driver.asc
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:29:```
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:30:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:31:The GitHub release contains a detached signature file for the NPM package (named
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:32:`mongodb-X.Y.Z.tgz.sig`).
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:33:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:34:The following command returns the link npm package.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:35:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:36:```shell
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:37:npm view mongodb@vX.Y.Z dist.tarball
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:38:```
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:39:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:40:Using the result of the above command, a `curl` command can return the official npm package for the release.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:41:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:42:To verify the integrity of the downloaded package, run the following command:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:43:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:44:```shell
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:45:gpg --verify mongodb-X.Y.Z.tgz.sig mongodb-X.Y.Z.tgz
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:46:```
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:47:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:48:> [!Note]
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:49:> No GPG verification is done when using npm to install the package. The contents of the GitHub tarball and npm's tarball are identical.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:50:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:51:Releases published to the npm registry also include a [provenance attestation](https://docs.npmjs.com/generating-provenance-statements), which cryptographically links the package to its source repository and build workflow. To verify provenance:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:52:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:53:```shell
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:54:npm audit signatures
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:55:```
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:56:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:57:The MongoDB Node.js driver follows [semantic versioning](https://semver.org/) for its releases.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:58:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:59:### Bugs / Feature Requests
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:60:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:61:Think you’ve found a bug? Want to see a new feature in `node-mongodb-native`? Please open a
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:62:case in our issue management tool, JIRA:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:63:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:64:- Create an account and login [jira.mongodb.org](https://jira.mongodb.org).
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:65:- Navigate to the NODE project [jira.mongodb.org/browse/NODE](https://jira.mongodb.org/browse/NODE).
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:66:- Click **Create Issue** - Please provide as much information as possible about the issue type and how to reproduce it.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:67:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:68:Bug reports in JIRA for all driver projects (i.e. NODE, PYTHON, CSHARP, JAVA) and the
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:69:Core Server (i.e. SERVER) project are **public**.
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:70:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:71:### Support / Feedback
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:72:
node_modules/mongodb/README.md:73:For issues with, questions about, or feedback for the Node.js driver, please look into our [support channels](https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/support). Please do not email any of the driver developers directly with issues or questions - you're more likely to get an answer on the [MongoDB Community Forums](https://community.mongodb.com/tags/c/drivers-odms-connectors/7/node-js-driver).
